D. Maintenance of Marine Navigational Beacon
In the coastal region, there are visual aids to support the marine navigation through the marking their location with lights at night: light house, light pole, beacon, light float, etc. Because visual aids to navigation should be sufficiently seen within the required range, marine officials must check and maintain their lights every night.
Small UAV with IR and night-vision camera can perform the maintenance instead of human very quickly. But it needs technical solution to 20 km flight over the coast in the night, and furthermore it must be able to detect and check the lights automatically.

