H. Detecting harmful air pollutants in emission gas
Many harmful pollutants are emitted from the chimneys in the industrial complex. Although the government oversees and controls them, it is difficult to collect and enforce pollutants quickly if people are directly involved in crackdowns. For this purpose, a small UAV equipped with a hyper-spectral camera needs to be operated for real-time air pollution scanning, and a system capable of collecting samples simultaneously when pollutant discharge is confirmed is being developed.

